column15: This email contains the feedback about your PA1 submission in the course
ECE 36800 Data Structures.  Your grade will be uploaded to Brightspace at
a later time after we have computed your scores.
Attached is a CSV file that contains the feedback. The content of this email
describes how to read the CSV file.  The log file CE_log.txt may also capture
messages (warning or error) from the compiler.  Errors stop an executable from
being generated.  So, you should pay attention to the error messages.  You may
see filenames that are not familiar.  These are files from the instructor so
that individual functions of your submission can be evaluated.
The feedback has been generated by an automatic grading script that tests your
submission files under several testing conditions.
Following discussion is about how to read the CSV file.
--- There are three groups of tests: "Array", "List", and "Sequence".
Within each of the first two groups, "pa1" tests all functions submitted by
you;  "Shellsort" tests only sorting; "Load" tests loading from file; "Save"
tests saving to file; and "main" tests the main function.
For the last group, it tests the sequence generation function.
--- For fields that denote a certain error, "0" means no such error, while "1"
or other positive numbers or words mean that the error exists. "-1" means no
result for this field is given because of another error. For example, if you
have a compile error, we cannot test whether your program has memory leak
or not.
--- "Compile error" means code cannot be compiled to get a executable program.
"Num of comp" denotes the number of comparison returned by the program. "Time
limit exceeded" means the program does not finish within a time limit.  When
it is negative, it means that your program aborted.  "Time(ms)" denotes how
long the program runs (if it does not abort or time-out). "No output file"
means no file of sorted result. "Wrong answer" means the sorted result is not
correct. The meanings of other fields are explained by their names.
--- The key is to get 0 for the columns "Wrong answer", "Stack overflow",
"Memory leak", and "Memory error", and in the case of sequence generation, 0 for
"Wrong sequence size".
If you see a compile error but are not sure why that would have occured, you

may come to my office hours so I can help you. Please note that there are files provided by the instructor in the compilation.  Therefore, you will see files that are not named "pa1.c", "sequence.c", "shell_array.c", or "shell_list.c".
If you have any questions or concerns, feel free to contact me via email or during office hours.
